fields.name: build
fields.comment: Current step of the buildstream process: `io` or `eem`

fields.name: step
fields.comment: Current substep of the buildstream. If `build=io`, these steps are `partition, calibrate, share, disaggregate`. If `build=eem`, these steps are ...

fields.name: region_level
fields.comment: Aggregation level to use when reading BEA GDP and Census Bureau data.

fields.name: sector_level
fields.comment: Aggregation level to use when reading BEA supply/use data.

fields.name: eem
fields.comment: Flag indicating whether to include the Energy-Environment module. If `eem=true`, first build `io` supply/use data. Then build `eem` data.

fields.name: save_build
fields.comment: Flag indicating decides whether to save the information at each build step. Setting `save_build=true` will add directories in the locations returned by [`SLiDE.datapath`](@ref). This feature is particularly helpful for buildstream debugging.

fields.name: overwrite
fields.comment: If data exists, do not read it. Build the data from scratch.

docstring: Information about CGE parameters used in the model.

fields.name: index
fields.comment: Sets on which the parameter depends
